OMG, this ice cream (actually frozen custard) is out of this world! It sent quivers throughout my body. Like many others, I doubled the salt (total of 1 tsp) and also substituted 5 yolks for 3 full eggs. I am a picky foodie, but this just became my favorite ice cream. It is rich, but I found that the addition of roasted pecans balances the richness and also provides the perfect crunch texture. It stays soft in the freezer which is also a bonus for homemade ice cream. Be careful when cooking the sugar to make the caramel. Black pans will make the melted sugar look darker than it is. This is NOT a bland ice cream, so reviewers that thought it was bland did not cook the sugar long enough to turn it into caramel. Just don't cook too long and burn it. I highly recommend that you go make this ice cream right now...go...do it...what are you waiting for?...seriously, do it.

