Rating: 4
I love this recipe, but have streamlined it. I put a cup of sugar in a 4 cup pyrex bowl with 1 TBs of water, mixed well. Microwave on high for 6 min., do not stir. Pour in 1 1/4 cps. of half and half, 2 tsp. of salt and a 1 tsp. of vanilla. The caramel will seize up, but just let it set and melt in the liquid. In another micro wave proof bowl, mix together 1/4 cup sugar, the three eggs and 2 cups of half and half, micro on high for 6 min., whisking half way through. Combine the caramel with the custard and chill. The whole process takes about 15 min.

