Rating: 4
Here's a tip for making the caramel: do it in the microwave. Combine the sugar with 1/4 cup water - just enought to wet the sugar - in a 4 cup Pyrex measuring cup and microwave it on high until it turns golden. Take it out when it is a couple of shades lighter than you want, as it will continue to darken. Wear gloves to protect your hands from the steam and add the cream, stirring, a little at a time. It will boil furiously. Continue adding cream and stirring until the sugar dissolves. If there's a little left on the spoon, use this spoon when stirring the custard - that will take care of the rest of it. Another tip: if you, like I, am a devotee of coffee ice cream, caramelizing half or all the sugar in the recipe will give it tremendous depth of flavor - much better than all white sugar would have ever done. We are huge ice cream fans and make ice creams year round; these are two of our faves.

