Excellent ice cream! I made 3/4s of the caramel, so it wouldn't be exceedingly sweet. Next time I might stop the caramel at a medium amber, because the sugar continues to cook after being removed from the heat - unless I shock it in an ice bath. Heating the cream before adding it to the sugar greatly reduces the splattering. Also, whipping half the sugar to the milk/cream mixture and the other half to the eggs will help reduce the chances of cooking the eggs, when tempering them. If the eggs go over 180'F they begin to curdle so I made sure to keep an eye on the temperature. Normally I make ice cream with just yolks, so this recipe was a nice surprise. Great flavor combination!

