Rating: 3
A little too sweet for me but, the deep caramel flavor is intense. I chilled both the caramel and custard separately in a double bowl of ice water and then put into ice cream maker. This cut the chilling period down to about 20 minutes. After 30 minutes in the ice cream maker, ice cream was thick enough to put into freezer for about 2 hours. I'll try next time with less sugar.

Rating: 4
Holy cow. This is delicious. It's like eating spoonfuls of really delicious caramel. It definitely needs the salt. In fact, I might almost add a little more than 1/2 teaspoon. But not much. My only beef is that the recipe isn't written very well. I haven't made custard in a year or so, and forgot that the burner needs to be VERY LOW after tempering the egg, otherwise you'll end up with a saucepot full of scrambled eggs. I tried to rush it and had to scrap it and start over. I just forgot that you can't rush this. Had the recipe pointed out what temperature to use, I probably wouldn't have done that. I'd just be concerned for folks who have never done it before and might make the same mistake.

